items.title: What a Bodega Taught the Socialist
items.description: Zohran Mamdani now says he wants to cut red tape for NYC small businesses. He should apply that epiphany across the board.

items.title: The True Toll of Conspiracy Theories
items.description: I witnessed Charlie Kirk’s murder. Conspiracy theorists are only making this heinous act worse.

items.title: The Feasts and Food of Advent
items.description: A season of joyful preparation leads us to Christmas.

items.title: So Jasmine Crockett Is Republicans’ Fault Now?
items.description: Media-amplified allegations that the GOP tricked her into running for Senate give the egotistical Texas rep far too little credit.

items.title: The Florida Highwaymen: Outsider Art, Tourism, and American Landscape
items.description: The fascinating story of black artists whose flamboyant colors, ocean waves, and swaying palms defined Florida for a generation of tourists.
